mindmap
  root((Infrastructure Planning for Enterprise AI))
    Enterprise Grade Requirements
      Heterogeneity by design
      Resilience and disaster recovery
      Observability across all artifacts
    Flexibility vs Governance
      Policy-driven adaptive infrastructure
      Self-service with governance overlays
      Centralized visibility and telemetry
    Strategic Multiplier
      Reduces marginal cost per model
      Compounds value through reuse
      Flywheel -- speed drives experimentation
    Cloud / On-Prem / Hybrid
      Cloud -- elastic, fast, ecosystem-rich
      On-prem -- control, residency, latency
      Hybrid -- unifying architecture required
    Ownership and Accountability
      Central platform teams as product teams
      Embedded infrastructure liaisons
      SLAs and change management rituals
    Blueprint and Roadmap
      Maturity model as milestone framework
      Capabilities mapped to real use cases
      Living strategy -- reviewed and evolved
    Legacy Modernization
      Wrap, isolate, phase out
      Parallel runs and rollback paths
      Organizational transformation, not just technical